The Credit Agreement is guaranteed by the Company’s wholly-owned U.S. subsidiaries. For the Term Loan, the Company is required to make quarterly principal payments of 1.25% of the original Term Loan ($3.1 million) through maturity, with the remaining balance due on September 12, 2023.

The fair value of borrowings under the Credit Agreement approximates book value because the interest rate is variable.

In addition, Pacific Insight was a party to a credit agreement with Roynat which was terminated during the second quarter of fiscal 2019. The fair value of other debt was $16.3 million at April 27, 2019 and was based on Level 2 inputs on a nonrecurring basis.
